d: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe pilgrims of Hajj and Umrah are the guests of Allah. He called them, and they answered him. They ask from Him, and He gives them.\u201d Source: Kashf al-Asta\u0304r 1075 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":23706,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/09\/07\/hajj-o-allah-forgive-pilgrims\/","url_meta":{"origin":31143,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Hajj: Forgive pilgrims, those they supplicate for","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 7, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cO Allah, forgive the pilgrims and those for whom the pilgrims seek forgiveness.\u201d Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Awsat\u0323 lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 8818 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Ibn Hajar \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15635,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/08\/14\/ihram-hajj-umrah-kalb\/","url_meta":{"origin":31143,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Ihram: Pilgrims may kill harmful animals if needed","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 14, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cFive animals are harmful and are lawful to kill while in a state of pilgrimage or otherwise: a snake, a speckled crow, a rat, a biting dog, and a kite.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1198 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15612,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/08\/07\/hajj-umrah-behalf-parents\/","url_meta":{"origin":31143,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Hajj: Perform Hajj and &#8216;Umrah for parents","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 7, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Fadl reported: A woman from the tribe of Khath\u2019am said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, my father is an old man and Allah has obligated him to perform the Hajj pilgrimage, but he cannot ride on the back of a camel.\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cPerform\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14299,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/20\/hajj-umrah-together\/","url_meta":{"origin":31143,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Hajj: Performing Hajj and Umrah together","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 20, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Subay ibn Ma\u2019bad reported: I raised my voice in preparation for both Umrah and Hajj together. Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cYou have been guided to the Sunnah\u00a0of your Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 1798 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3042,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/24\/pilgrims-makkah-madinah-quds\/","url_meta":{"origin":31143,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Pilgrimage: No religious travel but to Mecca, Medina, Jerusalem","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 24, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cDo not undertake a religious journey but to three mosques: the Sacred Mosque in Mecca, the Mosque of the Messenger of Allah, and the Furthest Mosque in Jerusalem.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1189, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1397 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/31143","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=31143"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/31143\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=31143"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=31143"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=31143"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}